.TH "sd_open" 9 "sd_open" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sd_open \- open a scsi disk device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sd_open
.BI "(struct block_device *bdev "  ","
.BI "fmode_t mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bdev" 12
Block device of the scsi disk to open
.IP "mode" 12
FMODE_* mask

Returns 0 if successful. Returns a negated errno value in case 
of error.
.SH "NOTE"
This can be called from a user context (e.g. fsck(1) )
or from within the kernel (e.g. as a result of a mount(1) ).
In the latter case \fIinode\fP and \fIfilp\fP carry an abridged amount
of information as noted above.

Locking: called with bdev->bd_mutex held.
